ss
Utility to investigate sockets

Args
-4/-6 list ipv4/ipv6 sockets
-n numeric addresses instead of hostnames
-l list listing sockets
-u/-t/-x list udp/tcp/unix sockets
-p Show process(es) that using socket

# show all listing tcp sockets including the corresponding process
ss -tlp

# show all sockets connecting to 192.168.2.1 on port 80
ss -t dst 192.168.2.1:80

# show all ssh related connection
ss -t state established '( dport = :ssh or sport = :ssh )'

#
ss -nlt

 ss -ta

# check what listen in port
ss -pnltu | grep 5432


The values set by autotuning can be seen via the Linux “ss” command from the iproute package (e.g. “ss -tmi”)

ss -4ntpl # check ipv4 listen connections


# current state of connections with ss -tan:

ss -tan | head -5

# Qty of conn en time-wait state
ss -tan state time-wait | wc -l
